      <article class="team__member">
        <div class="team__member-title team__member-title--viv">
          <h2 class="h2">Viv Slack - Co-Founder</h2>
        </div>
        <h4>Viv leads on the functional and technical aspects of the website, strategic direction of the organisation, & supporting the team.</h4>
        <p>Viv worked in web development for many years with major brands and charities, including Oxfam and Amnesty International. After 9 years at Manchester agency Code Computerlove, she left in 2015 to support local social enterprises to use technology to make a difference. Street Support Network emerged from conversations with local homeless people and frontline organisations about where they needed help. The rest is history. <a href="http://objectivesfirst.com">More about Viv</a></p>
      </article>

      <article class="team__member">
        <div class="team__member-title team__member-title--gary">
          <h2 class="h2">Gary Dunstan - Co-Founder</h2>
        </div>
        <h4>Gary leads on building and maintaining relationships with our partnerships, with a focus on businesses and supporting other cities, alongside strategy.</h4>
        <p>Gary has spent many years helping individuals and businesses with their ideas. Viv and Gary met at a social enterpreneurs event, and soon realised they shared the same core values, and complimentary skills. <a href="http://doinggoodthinking.com/">More about Gary</a></p>
      </article>

      <article class="team__member">
        <div class="team__member-title team__member-title--graham">
          <h2 class="h2">Graham Wood - Comms &amp; Marketing</h2>
        </div>
        <h4>Graham supports with communications and marketing for Street Support and <a href="https://charter.streetsupport.net/" title="Manchester Homelessness Partnership">Manchester Homelessness Partnership</a></h4>
        <p>Graham joined us in late 2017 through a work placement, and we were so impressed we asked him to stay. As well as a background in advertising and teaching, Graham has personal experience of homelessness, and also volunteers at The Booth Centre and Food4All.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="team__member">
        <div class="team__member-title team__member-title--olie">
          <h2 class="h2">Olie Martin - Network Support (GROW trainee)</h2>
        </div>
        <h4>Olie supports the network through independent peer-led research, managing site content, and writing articles.</h4>
        <p>Before experiencing homelessness, Olie studied Sociology &amp; Politics at Goldsmiths, University of London. As a result of his studies, as well as experiencing other social difficulties, studying and gaining experience through work, training and volunteering, he developed a strong passion for social justice and is honoured to work for an organisation like Street Support Network which shares his visions for a better society. After volunteering for Barnabus (Manchester), he found about this job and applied as he has lived experience within the realm of homelessness, whether that be on the streets themselves, in night shelters and hostels.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="team__member">
        <div class="team__member-title team__member-title--mark">
          <h2 class="h2">Mark Jepson - MHP Community Engagement Co-Ordinator</h2>
        </div>
        <h4>Mark supports people with lived experience of homelessness to participate in <a href="https://charter.streetsupport.net/" title="Manchester Homelessness Partnership">Manchester Homelessness Partnership</a>.</h4>
        <p>Mark worked with the Shelter Inspiring Change Manchester project for several years before joining Street Support Network, and has supported many people in the transition from homelessness back into independent living. He has personal experience of homelessness and complex needs, and a passion for co-production of services.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="team__member">
        <div class="team__member-title team__member-title--dee">
          <h2 class="h2">Dee Lowry - MHP Business Engagement Co-Ordinator</h2>
        </div>
        <h4>Dee works with businesses in Manchester to co-ordinate their support towards the aims of <a href="https://charter.streetsupport.net/" title="Manchester Homelessness Partnership">Manchester Homelessness Charter</a>.</h4>
        <p>Dee's career began overseas, working for international charities in programmes relating to equality, social enterprise, and poverty alleviation. She returned to Manchester in 2015, and has been involved with the homelessness sector ever since; volunteering and working with local charity Coffee4Craig. Dee brings experience in research and evaluation, and is focused on understanding and addressing causes in an inclusive way.</p>
      </article>

